    Letta Code: A Memory-First Coding Agent (#1 OSS on Terminal-Bench)

    Letta
    Letta
    3.47K subscribers
    8.5K views 2 days ago
    8,549 views Dec 16, 2025
    Introducing Letta Code: a memory-first coding agent and CLI harness, built on top of the Letta API. Instead of working in independent sessions, you work with a persisted agent that learns over time and is portable across models (Claude Sonnet/Opus, GPT-5, Gemini 3 Pro, GLM-4.6, and more). Letta Code is also highly performant - it is the #1 model-agnostic open source agent on Terminal-Bench, the leading AI coding benchmark. Read more about how to use Letta Code on the official docs page (https://docs.letta.com/letta-code), or check out the GitHub repo: https://github.com/letta-ai/letta-code Install Letta Code with: npm install -g @letta-ai/letta-code Timestamps: 0:00 Intro 0:20 Letta Code is a memory-first coding agent 2:00 Setting up Letta Code (installing, swapping agents/models, permissions) 4:32 Viewing your agents in the ADE 5:45 Agent Memory & Learning (/init and /remember) 11:33 Pinning (saving) agents 12:15 Skill Learning (skill creation demo) 19:10 Connect to ANY agent in the CLI 23:13 Models and toolsets 27:25 Outro
